article.description: Hayden Graham had 16 points, 12 rebounds and eight assists, and Air Force beat Robert Morris 64-52 on Sunday.
article.headline: Graham nears triple-double; Air Force beats Robert Morris
article.linkText: Graham nears triple-double; Air Force beats Robert Morris
article.story: AIR FORCE ACADEMY, Colo. -- Hayden Graham had 16 points, 12 rebounds and eight assists, and Air Force beat Robert Morris 64-52 on Sunday. Graham needed three assists in the final 6:17 to record Air Force's first triple-double in program history. Air Force went on a 14-2 run, with scoring from Ryan Manning, Zach Moer and Trevor Lyons, for a 55-41 lead with 4:15 remaining. Lyons finished with 14 points and Moer added 12 points with seven boards for Air Force (3-1). The Falcons shot just 38 percent from the field but outrebounded Robert Morris 47-36. Rodney Pryor had 25 points and 10 rebounds for Robert Morris (0-4). Elijah Minnie added 10 points and eight rebounds. The Colonials led 22-21 at halftime, and Isaiah Still and Minnie made 3-pointers at the start of the second half to extend their lead to 30-23. But Air Force answered with a 13-5 run for a 36-35 lead it wouldn't relinquish.
